<subSubSection id="EBAF651CC23F6F2EFF308D0AFBD55B2E" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A30A3697C23F6F2EFF308D0AFBD55B2E" blockId="14.[166,1225,1631,1850]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C23F6F2EFE928D0AFDA95A6D" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1927" box="[377,570,1631,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zernyi">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C23F6F2EFE928D0AFDA95A6D" box="[377,570,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Rhagoletis zernyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated from most species of 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C23F6F2EFBDA8D0AFB365A6D" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1862" box="[1073,1189,1631,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C23F6F2EFBDA8D0AFB365A6D" box="[1073,1189,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Rhagoletis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the characters given for the 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C23F6F2EFE018DD5FDF25A8D" authorityName="Marcovitch" authorityYear="1915" box="[490,609,1664,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juniperina">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C23F6F2EFE018DD5FDF25A8D" box="[490,609,1664,1689]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">juniperina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. It differs from the other species of that group by having yellow femora and the wing pattern with partially yellowish-brown discal and subapical bands that are broadly fused at anterior margin (other species have the wing pattern uniformly brown except 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C23F6F2EFE2F8DB5FDE35AED" box="[452,624,1759,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavigenualis">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C23F6F2EFE2F8DB5FE465AED" box="[452,469,1760,1785]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C23F6F2EFE098D8AFDE35AED" box="[482,624,1759,1785]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">flavigenualis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has the discal and subapical bands separated (
<figureCitation id="3B8E2A12C23F6F2EFF458DAAFF7B5B0D" box="[174,232,1791,1817]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[261,1137,1047,1737]" captionTargetId="figure-482@5.[253,1161,1027,1746]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Palearctic species of Rhagoletis species similar to R. merzi, wings: a — R. zernyi; b — R. flavigenualis; c — R. merzi, sp. n.; d — R. bagheera; e — R. batava. Bands are marked as follows: A — apical, D — discal, SA — subapical, SB — subbasal. Red arrow shows connection of D and SA; cyan arrow shows cr — crescentic hyaline area. Scale: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6456142" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6456142/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, b)); male and female genitalia not examined. Abdomen black with posterior halves of tergites creamy or yellow. Body length 4.0– 
<quantity id="644D9B72C23F6F2EFD7F8C4AFD7D5B2E" box="[660,750,1823,1850]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="4.8">4.8 mm</quantity>
; wing length Ơ = 
<quantity id="644D9B72C23F6F2EFC5D8C4AFBD15B2E" box="[950,1090,1823,1850]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.55" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="3.55" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="3.5">3.5–3.6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
